  <prompt>
    Design + apply the TestClock + seeded-Guid provider pattern to ≥1 test class in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/`. **No existing TestClock/IClock/ISystemClock/TimeProvider abstraction in `src/` — this is greenfield.** Per design.md §5.5 Track C intent, the src-side abstraction is the load-bearing scope: introduce an `IClock` (or equivalent) interface + default implementation in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/` (or shared `Spaarke.Core` if more appropriate), then wire the PoC test class to inject a `TestClock` implementation.

    Reference (read-only, NOT a template — these are test-internal TimeProvider uses that didn't propagate to src):
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Insights/Precedents/PrecedentProjectionSyncTests.cs`
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Insights/Ingest/IngestOrchestratorTests.cs`

    Target candidate: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/` (10 files / 4194 LOC; pick the highest-leverage file based on test-dependency analysis — likely a file whose tests currently have flake risk from time-of-day or Guid-randomness assumptions).

    Per D-04, this is **pilot-grade**: ONE test class converted to demonstrate the pattern. Pattern documentation is captured in this task's commit + cross-referenced by Phase 5 task 080 (which merges the pattern into `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md`).

    Per FR-13, the deliverables are: (a) at least 1 Workspace test class using the pattern; (b) pattern documentation drafted (Phase 5 task 080 merges into procedure doc); (c) r3 migration plan referenced.
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent introducing the TestClock + seeded-Guid abstraction in `Services/Workspace/` and demonstrating it in ≥1 test class.</role>

  <goal>
    Three deliverables:
    1. **Greenfield abstraction**: `IClock` (or equivalent — `ISystemClock`, `TimeProvider` adapter) + default implementation registered in DI, residing in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/` OR `src/server/shared/Spaarke.Core/` (decision depends on consumer breadth). Plus a seeded-Guid provider (`IGuidProvider` or similar) with default implementation.
    2. **PoC test class**: ≥1 existing test class in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/` updated to inject `TestClock` + `TestGuidProvider`, demonstrating deterministic time + ID assertions.
    3. **Pattern documentation draft**: a short markdown excerpt staged for Phase 5 task 080's merge into `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md`. Reference r3 migration plan: which other Workspace test classes are next, which Workspace src files need refactor.

    Acceptance per FR-13: PoC working in at least 1 Workspace test class; pattern doc draft exists; r3 migration plan referenced.
  </goal>

