  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §2.3 long-term item 13, deterministic test data is the path to lower flake rates and clearer time-based assertions. Microsoft introduced `TimeProvider` in .NET 8 as the canonical clock abstraction; some Spaarke test files already inject `TimeProvider` in test scope but the SRC side has not adopted any clock abstraction. This is the gap r2 Track C closes via a pilot.

      The Workspace area was chosen for the PoC because: (a) it has 10 files / 4194 LOC — enough surface to demonstrate the pattern; (b) it's not on the RB-T028 / RB-T044 hot paths (Phase 1-3 doesn't touch it); (c) its tests likely have time-based assertions (workspace timestamps, last-modified fields).

      Per D-04, this task ships the PoC — ONE test class showing the pattern works. r3 generalizes if r2 findings warrant it. The pattern doc draft from this task feeds directly into Phase 5 task 080 (which updates `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md` with both the ledger lifecycle section AND the TestClock pattern from this task).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="039" status="not-started">Phase 3 exit (all 20 ledger entries closed) — Phase 4 starts when Phase 3 exits</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/ (new IClock + IGuidProvider abstraction files; possibly shared/Spaarke.Core)</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/ (one test class converted to use TestClock + TestGuidProvider)</file>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/notes/testclock-pattern-draft.md (pattern doc draft for Phase 5 task 080)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read all 10 files in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/`; identify which use `DateTime.UtcNow`, `DateTimeOffset.UtcNow`, or `Guid.NewGuid()` directly (these are the candidates for the abstraction).</step>
    <step order="2">Read the 2 reference test files (PrecedentProjectionSyncTests.cs, IngestOrchestratorTests.cs) to see existing `TimeProvider` usage pattern. Decision: hand-roll `IClock` OR use `Microsoft.Extensions.Time.Testing` if available + register `TimeProvider` directly. Choose based on consumer fit + ADR-010 minimalism.</step>
    <step order="3">Read all test files in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/`; identify the highest-leverage test class to convert (one with the most time-based or Guid-based assertions; likely flake risk).</step>
    <step order="4">Create the abstraction file(s) in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/` (or `src/server/shared/Spaarke.Core/` if cross-module). Choose between hand-rolled `IClock` interface OR direct `TimeProvider` adoption. Register in DI (`Program.cs` or scoped Workspace DI module).</step>
    <step order="5">Refactor target Workspace src file(s) (1-2 max) to consume the new abstraction via constructor injection; replace direct `DateTime.UtcNow` / `Guid.NewGuid()` calls.</step>
    <step order="6">Refactor target test class to inject `TestClock` + `TestGuidProvider`; assert against deterministic values; remove any flake-prone time/Guid assertions.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Workspace"` to verify the converted class + adjacent Workspace tests still pass. Run the full suite at least once to verify no regression elsewhere.</step>
    <step order="8">Draft `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/notes/testclock-pattern-draft.md` documenting: abstraction signature, DI registration, TestClock + TestGuidProvider test-side implementations, when to use the pattern, r3 migration plan (next Workspace tests to convert).</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 — Run `code-review` + `adr-check` against the new files (FULL rigor mandatory per ADR-010 + greenfield abstraction). Address any HIGH findings before commit.</step>
    <step order="10">Verify `git status` shows only: new abstraction file(s) in `src/`; refactored Workspace src file(s); refactored test class; pattern draft doc. Commit: "test(workspace): TestClock + seeded-Guid PoC pattern in Services/Workspace/* (FR-13)".</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">enumerate Workspace src + tests; reference TimeProvider files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">refactor target Workspace src file + test class</tool>
    <tool name="Write">new abstraction file(s) in src/; pattern draft doc</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Workspace"`; full suite verification; `git status`; final commit</tool>
    <tool name="Skill">code-review (Step 9.5); adr-check (Step 9.5)</tool>
  </tools>

